info.name: GWS-DOCS
info.description:
# Introduction
SBC - Global Web Services allows you to expose Specialized specific data to external parties like POS application, Web Shops, etc.

SBC - Global Web Services contains the following web services:

 - Product Catalog
 - Product Availability
 - Serial Number Details
 - Purchase Order
 - Order Details
 - Search Transactions 
 - Daily Sale
 - Stock Info ASN / Shipment Details 	
 - Invoice Details – not available yet 	
 - Credit Availability – not available yet 	
	
Supporting web services:
 - Address Information – not available yet


# Overview
Things that the developers should know about

# Authentication
What is the preferred way of using the API?
Basic Authentication

| Field Name | DataType | Required | Description  |
|------|----------|-------------|---|
| Username| string |         Y    | This field is the dealer or POS username, which specialized provides.  |
| Password | string |         N    | This field is the dealer or POS password, which specialized provides.  |
| AccountNumber | string |     Y        |  This field will be populated with the B2B Dealer Account Number associated with the request (if applicable). |
| Lang | string |        N     | ISO 2-digit language code  |
| Country | string |      Y       | ISO 2-digit country code |
| SourceApp | string |     Y        | This is constant value of "POS".  |

# Error Codes
What errors and status codes can a user expect?

# Rate limit
Is there a limit to the number of requests an user can send?
There is no rate limitation for the api

query.description: ID = simple response; ITEM_DETAIL = detailed response

request.description:
This web service returns product catalog details.

> When the web service is invoked by the external party, it needs to specify the level of detail to be returned. `ResultFormat` specifies the level of detail required in the response. It’s also possible to return the item availability based upon the parameters send.

> To avoid all (active) items to be send within one single request and response, the external application needs to request a range of items in Pagination pattern. The request will get a `PageIndex` and `ItemsPerPage`. By this way the external party can get all items in several requests.

request.description:
This web services provides the external party with the actual item availability of one or more items. 

| Field Name | Description |
|--|--|
|Availability.WhseCode| This field will contain the Warehouse Name for the current availability record. |
|Availability.AvailableQuantity| The AvailableQuantity object will contain the real time onhand quantity of the item available in the Speicialized ERP system. |
|ItemPrice.SellingPrice|The Selling Price object will contain PriceAmount and BaseQuantity object indicating the Price and Base Quantity associated with the pricing record.|

request.description:
This web services provides the external party with the order details.

> Please note that either OrderNumber is required or CustPoNumber is required. One of the elements must contain a value.

| Field Name | DataType | Required |Description |
|--|--|--|--|
|OrderNumber| String |N|Specialized Oracle number returned from the order create webservice. |
|CustPoNumber|  String |N|This field contains a reference to the Purchase Order in the external party’s application. The string is allowed a size of 50 characters maximum. This could be external system order number. |
|PageIndex|  String |Y|This field refers to current page, if the order details requested spans to multiple pages. |
|OrdersPerPage| String |Y|This field refers to the maximum numer of orders that can be fetched for a dealer in a single call. |
